      "content": {
        "summary": "Subject to the articles or by-laws, a majority of the directors, or the minimum number required by the articles, constitutes directors' quorum; if fewer than three directors, all directors must be present.",
        "tooltip": "Use the articles and by-laws first, then apply the OBCA directors' quorum default and the all-directors rule for boards under three.",
        "caveat": "Vacancies and articles/by-laws can affect whether remaining directors may act.",
        "displayCitation": "OBCA s.126(3)-(5)"
      },
      "priority": 34
